<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p><strong>Last updated:</strong>29/11/2025</p>

<h2>1. About this policy</h2>
<p>
    QuickToolbox (“the Website”, “we”, “us”) provides free online tools such as text utilities, calculators and 
    other simple web-based functions. This Privacy Policy explains what personal data we collect, how we use it, 
    and your rights under UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018.
</p>

<h2>2. What data we collect</h2>
<p>We collect minimal personal data and only for the purposes described below.</p>

<h3>2.1. Data you provide directly</h3>
<p>
    QuickToolbox does <strong>not</strong> collect or store any personal data you enter into our tools. 
    All calculations (such as text formatting or loan calculations) happen in your browser and 
    are <strong>not sent to our server</strong>.
</p>

<h3>2.2. Automatically collected data</h3>
<p>When you visit the Website, standard technical information may be logged:</p>
<ul>
    <li>IP address (anonymised where supported by analytics tools)</li>
    <li>Browser type and version</li>
    <li>Device type</li>
    <li>Pages visited</li>
    <li>Time spent on pages</li>
    <li>Referring website</li>
</ul>
<p>This information is used solely for analytics and improving the Website.</p>

<h3>2.3. Cookies</h3>
<p>We use two categories of cookies:</p>

<p><strong>Essential cookies</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Used to remember cookie-consent preferences</li>
    <li>Required for the website to function</li>
    <li>Cannot be disabled</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Optional cookies (only if you accept them)</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Google Analytics (measuring traffic and performance)</li>
    <li>Google AdSense (advertising and personalisation)</li>
</ul>

<p>
    Optional cookies are <strong>not loaded</strong> unless you click 
    <em>“Accept”</em> on our cookie banner.
</p>
<p>For full details, see our <a href="/CookiePolicy">Cookie Policy</a>.</p>

<h2>3. How we use your data</h2>
<p>We use collected data for:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Improving tools and Website performance</li>
    <li>Measuring usage of tools</li>
    <li>Ensuring website security</li>
    <li>Running advertising (if enabled)</li>
    <li>Handling cookie-consent choices</li>
</ul>

<p>We do <strong>not</strong>:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Sell your data</li>
    <li>Share your data with third parties for marketing</li>
    <li>Profile individual users</li>
    <li>Store tool input data</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Legal basis for processing</h2>
<p>Under UK GDPR, our processing relies on:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Consent</strong> — for optional cookies (analytics/ads)</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — ensuring site security and performance</li>
    <li><strong>Legal obligations</strong> — maintaining standard server logs</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Third-party services we use</h2>

<h3>5.1 Google Analytics</h3>
<p>Used to measure traffic and understand Website usage. IP anonymisation is enabled where possible.</p>

<h3>5.2 Google AdSense (if enabled)</h3>
<p>
    Used to display adverts and measure advertising performance. 
    Ad personalisation occurs only if you consent.
</p>

<p>Each provider has its own privacy controls:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank">Google Analytics Opt-Out</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Data retention</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Essential logs are retained for up to 12 months</li>
    <li>Cookie-consent preferences are stored locally in your browser until removed</li>
    <li>No tool-input data is stored or retained</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
<p>
    QuickToolbox is not aimed at children under 13. 
    We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.
</p>

<h2>8. Your rights</h2>
<p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Access your personal data</li>
    <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
    <li>Request deletion where applicable</li>
    <li>Object to processing</li>
    <li>Withdraw consent for optional cookies at any time</li>
</ul>

<p>
    To change your cookie settings, use the 
    <a href="#" onclick="localStorage.removeItem('qt-cookie-consent'); location.reload();">
        Change cookie settings
    </a> 
    link in the footer.
</p>

<h2>9. Data storage & security</h2>
<p>
    The Website is hosted on servers located in the UK or EU. 
    We apply standard technical measures to keep the Website secure. 
    No financial or personally identifiable information is stored.
</p>

<h2>10. Contact</h2>
